  "text": "• Cervical spondylosis: Hand paresthesia is a frequent and early symptom found in patients either with cervical spondylosis or carpal tunnel syndrome [CITATION_1] . In cervical spondylosis, paresthesia is not commonly nocturnal, aggravated by hand activity, or associated with hand pain, in contrast to carpal tunnel syndrome [CITATION_2] .",
